<h2>What Is SEO and Why Does It Matter for Kenyan Businesses?</h2>
<p>SEO (Search Engine Optimisation) is the process of making your website appear higher in Google search results — so when a potential customer in Nairobi, Mombasa, or Kisumu searches for your type of business, they find you before they find your competitors.</p>
<p>The power of SEO is that the traffic is free. Unlike Google Ads, where you pay for every click, organic search rankings generate leads continuously without ongoing spend. For Kenyan SMEs with limited marketing budgets, it's one of the highest-ROI channels available.</p>

<h2>How Google Decides Who Ranks at the Top</h2>
<p>Google's algorithm considers hundreds of factors, but the most important can be grouped into three categories:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Relevance</strong> — does your page actually answer what the searcher is looking for?</li>
  <li><strong>Authority</strong> — do other websites link to yours? Is your business established and trusted?</li>
  <li><strong>Technical quality</strong> — is your site fast, secure, mobile-friendly, and easy for Google to crawl?</li>
</ul>
<p>A good SEO strategy addresses all three. Focusing on just one won't get you to the top.</p>

<h2>The Four Pillars of SEO in Kenya</h2>
<h3>1. Keyword Research</h3>
<p>You need to rank for the words and phrases your customers actually type into Google. In Kenya, this means understanding local search patterns — for example, "plumber Nairobi" gets 30x more searches than "plumbing services Kenya." We research the exact terms your target customers use and build your SEO strategy around them.</p>

<h3>2. On-Page Optimisation</h3>
<p>On-page SEO is what you control directly on your website — your page titles, headings, content, images, and internal links. Every page that targets a keyword needs:</p>
<ul>
  <li>A clear, keyword-rich title tag (under 60 characters)</li>
  <li>A compelling meta description (under 160 characters)</li>
  <li>A clear H1 heading</li>
  <li>Quality content that answers the searcher's intent</li>
  <li>Internal links to related pages on your site</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Technical SEO</h3>
<p>Technical SEO ensures Google can find, crawl, and index your website correctly. Key technical factors:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Site speed (especially on mobile — Google's Core Web Vitals)</li>
  <li>HTTPS (SSL certificate)</li>
  <li>Correct sitemap and robots.txt</li>
  <li>No broken links or duplicate content</li>
  <li>Structured data (schema markup) for rich results</li>
</ul>

<h3>4. Local SEO</h3>
<p>For Kenyan businesses serving a specific area, local SEO is the most important channel. This means:</p>
<ul>
  <li>A fully optimised Google Business Profile</li>
  <li>Consistent NAP (Name, Address, Phone) across the web</li>
  <li>Local keyword targeting ("accountant Westlands Nairobi")</li>
  <li>Customer reviews on Google</li>
</ul>

